Peter Dada, Akure Two men were reportedly killed in two separate incidents in Ondo State on Monday by some yet-to-be-identified persons suspected to be gunmen. The deceased were a security guard, Mr. Jimoh Teloye; and a retired school principal, Mr. Christopher Karigidi. According to a source, Teloye was a night guard employed by some shop owners in Ikare Akoko, headquarters of Akoko North-East Local Government Area of Ondo State. His body was found on the ground on Monday morning, with his hands tied. The source said, “Those having shops behind the central mosque got to their shops this morning (Monday) and met the man on the ground, dead. “His hands were tied. There was an indication that he was strangled to death by the hoodlums because there was no gunshot wounds or marks on his body. “After killing him, they broke the shops with a big hammer and other objects and made off with some items.” The death of Mr. Karigidi occurred in Ode Irele, headquarters of Irele Local Government Area of the state, on Monday morning . Karigidi, who was described as a retired principal and and Lay President of the Methodist Church of Nigeria, Igbobini Diocese, was reportedly killed by hoodlums in his residence early Monday morning. It was gathered that the killers invaded the deceased’s house at about 3am on Monday and carried out the dastardly act. When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer in the state command, Mr. Femi Joseph, confirmed the two incidents and said the command had commenced investigations into the two killings. “We have begun investigation into the matter and we will soon arrest those behind the ungodly acts,” Joseph stated. He added that the remains of the deceased had been deposited at the morgues.